servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrot{3%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were
3 inches long and 1⁄3 inch thick).

Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1%unit}.

Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise; lay flat and cut into
½-inch-thick sticks.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Lay tortillas on a clean work surface.

Evenly spread @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} on tortillas. Arrange 1-2
@sliced turkey breast{8%ounce} slices in a single layer on each tortilla.

> TIP: We sent more turkey! Use as many or as few slices as you like.

Top with cucumber sticks.

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create roll-ups. Halve
roll-ups.

To serve: Serve turkey roll-ups with carrot sticks, apple slices, and
@hummus{3/4%cup} on the side.

To stash: Refrigerate turkey roll-ups, carrot sticks, apple slices, and
hummus in separate containers and pack as desired.